  "prompt": "What exactly is 'pins and needles?",
  "response": "\"Pins and needles\" is a common phrase used to describe the tingling sensation that people often experience in their limbs, typically in the arms, legs, fingers, or feet. This sensation can occur when pressure is applied to a nerve, such as when you sit or lie in one position for too long, leading to temporary nerve compression. \n\nWhen the pressure is relieved, blood flow returns to the affected area, and the nerves start to regain normal function, often resulting in that tingling feeling, which can also be described as prickling or a crawling sensation. This phenomenon is medically known as \"paresthesia.\"\n\nWhile pins and needles are usually harmless and temporary, persistent or recurrent sensations can sometimes indicate underlying medical conditions, such as nerve damage, diabetes, or multiple sclerosis, among others. If someone experiences prolonged or painful episodes of pins and needles, it is advisable to consult a healthcare professional.",
